    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Colorless crystal or soft, white, alkaline powder prepared by reacting calcium oxide (lime) with water in a process called slaking. It is used in paints, dehairing hide, medicines, and in conservation for superficial protective treatments thanks to its conversion into calcium carbonate.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
